title: 2017 KTM 200 Duke launched in India at Rs 1.43 lakh : New Launches, News - India Today
text:
2017 KTM 200 Duke launched in India at Rs 1.43 lakh IndiaToday.in | New Delhi, February 23, 2017 | Written by Pratik Rakshit | UPDATED 14:01 IST The 2017 KTM 200 Duke rivals the Honda CBR 150R and Bajaj Pulsar RS 200 in India. 
KTM on Thursday launched the much-speculated 200 Duke in India at Rs 1.43 lakh (ex showroom, New Delhi). Amid much speculation that KTM had discontinued the popular 200 Duke, the company launched the 2017 KTM 200 Duke in India to catch up sales in the country. The bookings for the 2017 KTM 200 Duke commenced today with deliveries to start from March. 
Design: 
In terms of looks, the 2017 KTM 200 Duke remains unchanged from the previous generation. Apart from revised decals, the new 200 Duke gets no design elements from its older sibling, the 2017 KTM 390 Duke. 2017 KTM 200 Duke 
Engine: 
The Duke 200 comes with a 199.5 cc, single-cylinder, liquid cooled, petrol engine, that produces peak power at 25 bhp and peak torque of 19 Nm, mated to a six-speed gearbox with a wet multi-disc clutch. 2017 KTM 200 Duke 
Features: 
The new 2017 KTM 200 Duke gets a new LED headlight, a new digital instrument cluster along with disc brakes at front and rear. Moreover, the 200 Duke also gets inverted front forks and monoshock at the back. 2017 KTM 200 Duke 
Dimensions: 
The 2017 KTM 200 Duke comes with a wheelbase of 1367 mm and measures 2050 mm in length, 730 mm in width and 810 mm in height. It also has a ground clearance of 178 mm and a fuel efficiency of 35Kmpl. 2017 KTM 200 Duke 
Competition: 
The 2017 KTM 200 Duke rivals the Honda CBR 150R and Bajaj Pulsar RS 200 in India.
